        }
      ],
      "orig": "We picked the mo del parameter configuration that pro duced the b est prediction\nquality (enc=6, dec=6, heads=8) with PubTabNet alone, then independently\ntrained and evaluated it on three publicly available data sets: PubTabNet (395k\nsamples), FinTabNet (113k samples) and PubTables-1M (about 1M samples).\nPerformance results are presented in Table. 2. It is clearly evident that the model\ntrained on OTSL outperforms HTML across the board, keeping high TEDs and\nmAP scores even on di ffi cult financial tables (FinTabNet) that contain sparse\nand large tables.",
      "text": "We picked the mo del parameter configuration that pro duced the b est prediction\nquality (enc=6, dec=6, heads=8) with PubTabNet alone, then independently\ntrained and evaluated it on three publicly available data sets: PubTabNet (395k\nsamples), FinTabNet (113k samples) and PubTables-1M (about 1M samples).\nPerformance results are presented in Table. 2. It is clearly evident that the model\ntrained on OTSL outperforms HTML across the board, keeping high TEDs and\nmAP scores even on di ffi cult financial tables (FinTabNet) that contain sparse\nand large tables."
    },
    {
      "self_ref": "#/texts/12",
      "parent": {
        "$ref": "#/body"
      },
      "children": [],
      "content_layer": "body",
      "label": "text",
      "prov": [
